{"name": "zyte-api", "metadata": {"name": "zyte-api", "version": "0.6.0", "classifiers": ["Development Status :: 3 - Alpha", "Intended Audience :: Developers", "License :: OSI Approved :: BSD License", "Natural Language :: English", "Operating System :: OS Independent", "Programming Language :: Python :: 3", "Programming Language :: Python :: 3.10", "Programming Language :: Python :: 3.11", "Programming Language :: Python :: 3.8", "Programming Language :: Python :: 3.9"], "home_page": "https://github.com/zytedata/python-zyte-api", "license": null, "documentation_url": null, "dependencies": ["aiohttp", "attrs", "brotli", "runstats", "tenacity", "tqdm", "w3lib"], "summary": "Python interface to Zyte API", "upload_time": 1716990637}, "documentation": ["# python-zyte-api\n\n```{image} https://img.shields.io/pypi/v/zyte-api.svg\n:alt: PyPI Version\n:target: https://pypi.python.org/pypi/zyte-api\n```\n\n```{image} https://img.shields.io/pypi/pyversions/zyte-api.svg\n:alt: Supported Python Versions\n:target: https://pypi.python.org/pypi/zyte-api\n```\n\n```{image} https://github.com/zytedata/python-zyte-api/actions/workflows/test.yml/badge.svg\n:alt: Build Status\n:target: https://github.com/zytedata/python-zyte-api/actions/workflows/test.yml\n```\n\n```{image} https://codecov.io/github/zytedata/zyte-api/coverage.svg?branch=master\n:alt: Coverage report\n:target: https://codecov.io/gh/zytedata/zyte-api\n```\n\n% description-start\n\nCommand-line client and Python client library for [Zyte API].\n\n% description-end\n\n## Installation\n\n% install-start\n\n```shell\npip install zyte-api\n```\n\n:::{note}\nPython 3.8+ is required.\n:::\n\n% install-end\n\n## Basic usage\n\n% basic-start\n\n### Set your API key\n\n% key-get-start\n\nAfter you [sign up for a Zyte API account](https://app.zyte.com/account/signup/zyteapi), copy [your API key](https://app.zyte.com/o/zyte-api/api-access).\n\n% key-get-end\n\n### Use the command-line client\n\nThen you can use the zyte-api command-line client to send Zyte API requests.\nFirst create a text file with a list of URLs:\n\n```none\nhttps://books.toscrape.com\nhttps://quotes.toscrape.com\n```\n\nAnd then call `zyte-api` from your shell:\n\n```shell\nzyte-api url-list.txt --api-key YOUR_API_KEY --output results.jsonl\n```\n\n### Use the Python sync API\n\nFor very basic Python scripts, use the sync API:\n\n```python\nfrom zyte_api import ZyteAPI\n\nclient = ZyteAPI(api_key=\"YOUR_API_KEY\")\nresponse = client.get({\"url\": \"https://toscrape.com\", \"httpResponseBody\": True})\n```\n\n### Use the Python async API\n\nFor asyncio code, use the async API:\n\n```python\nimport asyncio\n\nfrom zyte_api import AsyncZyteAPI\n\n\nasync def main():\n    client = AsyncZyteAPI(api_key=\"YOUR_API_KEY\")\n    response = await client.get(\n        {\"url\": \"https://toscrape.com\", \"httpResponseBody\": True}\n    )\n\n\nasyncio.run(main())\n```\n\n% basic-end\n\nRead the [documentation](https://python-zyte-api.readthedocs.io) for more\ninformation.\n\n- Documentation: <https://python-zyte-api.readthedocs.io>\n- Source code: <https://github.com/zytedata/python-zyte-api>\n- Issue tracker: <https://github.com/zytedata/python-zyte-api/issues>\n\n[zyte api]: https://docs.zyte.com/zyte-api/get-started.html\n"], "modules": [{"name": "zyte_api.errors", "documentation": [], "functions": [], "variables": [], "classes": [{"name": "zyte_api.errors.ParsedError", "bases": [], "methods": [{"name": "zyte_api.errors.ParsedError.from_body", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "cls", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "response_body", "type": {"name": "bytes", "xref": {"fqname": "functions.bytes", "project": "--std--"}, "params": null}, "default": null}], "returns": {"name": "ParsedError", "xref": {"fqname": "zyte_api.errors.ParsedError", "project": null}, "params": null}, "documentation": ["Return a {class}`ParsedError` object built out of the specified\nerror response body.\n"]}, {"name": "zyte_api.errors.ParsedErro